<A NAME="eolPage33"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Critical Accounting Policies
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	and Estimates
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The preparation of financial statements in conformity with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	U.S. GAAP
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	requires that management
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	apply accounting policies and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	make estimates
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and assumptions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	that affect the results of operations and the amounts of assets and liabilities reported in the financial statements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	as well as related disclosures.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Management discusses these policies, estimates and assumptions with its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	accounting and disclosure governance committee on a regular basis and provides periodic updates on management decisions to the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	udit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	C
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ommittee of the Landauer
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	B
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	oard of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	D
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	irectors.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Critical accounting policies are those that are most important to the portrayal of a company&#x2019;s financial condition and results
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	of operations
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, and that require management&#x2019;s most difficult, subjective or complex judgments, often as a result of the need to make estimates about the effect of matters that are inherently uncertain.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We believe that
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the application of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the accounting policies
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	described below
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	require significant judgments and estimates on the part of mana
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	gement
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	in the preparation of the Company&#x2019;s financial statements and accompanying notes.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	For a summary of our significant accounting policies, including the accounting poli
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	cies discussed below, see Note 1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	to the Consolidated Financial Statements.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Revenue Recognition and Deferred Contract Revenue
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The majority of Radiation Measurement revenues are realized from radiation measurement services and other services incidental to radiation dose measurement. The measuring and monitoring services provided by the Company to its customers are of a subscription nature and are continuous. The Company views its business in the Radiation Measurement segment as services provided to customers over a period of time and the wear period is the period over which those services are provided. Badge production, wearing of badges, badge analysis, and report preparation are integral to the benefit that the Company provides to its customers. These services are provided to customers on an agreed-upon recurring basis (monthly, bi-monthly, quarterly, semi-annually or annually) that the custom
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	er chooses for the wear period.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Revenue is recognized on a straight-line basis
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	over the wear period.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Revenues are recognized over the periods in which the customers wear the badges irrespective of whether invo
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	iced in advance or in arrears.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	To a lesser degree, the Company provides equipment and sells badges to smaller distrib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	utors and joint ventures.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Radiation Measurement segment product revenues are recognized upon delivery of goods when title and risk of loss pass to customers.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company, through its Medical Physics segment, offers full scope medical physics services to hospitals and radiation therapy centers. Services offered include, but are not limited to, clinical physics support in radiation oncology, commissioning services, special projects support and imaging physics services. Delivery of medical physics services can be of a contracted, recurring nature or as a discrete project with a defined service outcome. Recurring services often are provided on the customer
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s premises by a full-time employee or fraction of a full-time employee. These services are recognized as revenue on a straight-line basis over the life of the contract unless there is another discernable pattern as the services are rendered. Fee for service revenue is recognized when the service is delivered.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Contracted services are billed on an agreed-upon recurring basis, either in advance or arrears of the service being delivered. Customers may be billed monthly, quarterly, or at some other regular interval over the contracted period. The amounts recorded as deferred
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	contract
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	revenue represent invoiced amounts in advance of delivery of the service. Management believes that the amount of deferred contract revenue fairly represents remaining business activity with customers invoiced in advance. Fee for service revenue is typically associated with much shorter contract periods, or with discrete individual projects, and revenue is recognized upon completion of the project and customer acceptance.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Medical Products business was divested in May 2016.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Medical Products segment offer
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	a broad product portfolio ranging from consumables used with MRI, CT, and mammography technologies to highly engineered consumable passive reflective markers used during image guided surgery procedures. The Medical Products segment recognize
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	d
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	revenues upon shipment or delivery of goods when title and risk of loss pass to customers.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>

</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage34"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Property, Plant &amp; Equipment and Other Assets
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Maintenance and repairs are charged to expense and renewals and betterments are capitalized. Plant and equipment and other assets, primarily dosimetry badges, are recorded at cost and are depreciated or amortized on a straight-line basis over the estimated useful lives, which are primarily 30 years for buildings, 3 to 8 years for equipment, 5 to 10 years for internal software and 30 months to 8 years for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	dosimetry devices
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. The Company assesses the carrying value and the remaining useful lives of its property, plant, equipment and other assets when events or circumstances indicate the carrying value may not be recoverable or the estimated useful life may no longer be appropriate. Factors that could trigger this review
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	include competitive conditions, government regulati
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ons and technological changes.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Any change in the carrying value or estimated useful lives of property, plant, equipment and other assets could materially impact the Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	results of operation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	financial position and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	liquidity.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;BACKGROUND-COLOR:YELLOW;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company capitalizes costs of software which is acquired, internally developed, or modified solely to meet
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the Company&#x2019;s internal needs.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Internal and external costs incurred to develop internal-use computer software during the application development stage are capitalized. Costs incurred during the preliminary project stage as well as training costs and maintenance costs during the post implementation-operation stage are expensed. Capitalized costs of software amounted to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$0.4 million and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	0.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million for fiscal 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Goodwill and Other Intangible Assets
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company&#x2019;s intangible assets include purchased customer lists, licenses, patents, trademarks, tradenames and goodwill. Purchased customer lists are recorded at cost and are amortized on a straight-line basis over estimated useful lives, which range from 4 to 15 years. Patents and licenses are also recorded at cost and are amortized on a straight-line basis over their useful lives, which range from 10 to 20 years. Tradenames have both definite lives up to 10 years and indefinite lives. The Company acquired goodwill primarily from its acquisitions of Landauer-Europe, SAPRA-Landauer, LMP
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and IZI
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Medical Products, LLC
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	(which was part of the Medical Products business divested in May 2016)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	as well as other smaller investments. Goodwill has an indefinite life.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Goodwill and certain intangible assets with indefinite lives are reviewed annually for impairment and more frequently if
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	an event occurs or circumstances change that would require the Company to perform an interim review
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company has three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	reporting units
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	: Radiation Measurement; Medical Physics; and Medical Products.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Goodwill impairment testing first requires a comparison between the carrying value and fair value of a reporting
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	unit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	with associated goodwill. Carrying value is based on the assets and liabilities associated with the operations of that reporting
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	unit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. The Company estimates the fair value of the reporting
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	units
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	using the income approach and the market approach. If the Company believes that the fair value of a reporting
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	unit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	exceeds its carrying value by a substantial margin, the Company may perform a qualitative analysis instead.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	If the fair value of a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	reporting unit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	exceeds its carrying amount, goodwill of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	reporting unit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	is considered not to be impaired and the second step of the impairment test is unnecessary. If the carrying amount of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	reporting unit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	exceeds its fair value, the second step of the goodwill impairment test is performed to measure the amount of the impairment loss, if any. The second step of the goodwill impairment test compares the implied fair value of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	reporting unit&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	goodwill with the carrying amount of that goodwill. If the carrying amount of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	reporting unit&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	goodwill exceeds the implied fair value of that goodwill, an impairment loss is recognized in an amount equal to that excess. The implied fair value of goodwill is determined in the same manner as the amount of goodwill recognized in a business combination. That is, the fair value of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	reporting unit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	is allocated to all of the assets and liabilities of that
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	reporting unit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	(including any unrecognized intangible assets) as if the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	reporting unit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	had been acquired in a business combination, and the fair value of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	reporting unit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	was the purchase price paid to acquire the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	reporting unit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;LINE-HEIGHT:110%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	34
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage35"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;LINE-HEIGHT:110%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company estimated the fair value of the Radiation Measurement
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Medical Physics reporting
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	units
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	as of September 30, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	using the income approach and the market approach, and no impairment charges resulted. In the income approach, the Company utilized a discounted cash flow analysis, which involved estimating the expected after-tax cash flows that will be generated by the reporting segments and then discounting these cash flows to present value reflecting the relevant risks associated with the reporting
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	unit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and the time value of money. This approach requires the use of significant estimates and assumptions, including long-term projections of future cash flows, market conditions, discount rates reflecting the risk inherent in future cash flows, revenue growth, perpetual growth rates and profitability, among others.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The market approach is primarily comprised of comparable companies. This approach compares the subject segment to selected reasonably similar companies whose securities are actively traded in the public markets. For companies providing services similar to those provided by the Company, the income and market approaches will generally provide the most reliable indications of value because the value of such companies is more dependent on their ability to generate earnings than on the value of the individual assets.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company completed an impairment test for Medical Products as of June 30, 2014 when it became apparent that anticipated revenue and profitability trends in Medical Products were not being achieved to the extent forecasted. Based on the testing performed, the Company recorded a non-cash impairment charge of $62.2 million, of which $41.4 million related to goodwill and $20.8 million related to intangible assets for the fiscal year ended September 30, 2014.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;The Medical Products business was divested in May 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Intangible assets represent purchased assets that lack physical substance but can be distinguished from goodwill. The Company uses valuation techniques in estimating the initial fair value of acquired intangible assets. These valuations are primarily based on the present value of the estimated net cash flows expected to be derived from the intangible assets, discounted for assumptions such as future customer attrition. The Company evaluates intangible assets for impairment annually or whenever events or changes in circumstances indicate that the carrying amount of the assets may not be recoverable. Therefore, changes such as higher or earlier-than-expected customer attrition or obsolescence of technology may result in higher future amortization charges or an impairment charge for intangible assets. See Note
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	to the Consolidated Financial Statements for additional information regarding the value of goodwill and other intangible assets.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Income Taxes
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company estimates the income tax provision for income taxes that are currently payable and records deferred
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	income
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	tax assets and liabilities for the temporary differences in tax consequences between the financial statements and tax returns. Temporary differences result from, among other events, revenues, expenses, gains, or losses that are included in taxable income of an earlier or later year than the year in which they are recognized in financial statement income. These deferred
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	income
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	tax assets and liabilities are measured using enacted tax rates expected to apply to taxable income
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	in the years in which those temporary differences are expected to be recovered or settled. To the extent that deferred
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	income
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	tax assets will not likely be recovered from future taxable income, a valuation allowance is established ag
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ainst such deferred
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	income
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	tax assets.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company has no indefinite reinvestment assertions on its foreign earnings and profits.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Management exercises significant judgment in the valuation of its current and deferred
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	income
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	tax assets and liabilities. The Company recognizes the financial statement effects of its tax positions in its current and deferred
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	income
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	tax assets and liabilities when it is more likely than not that the position will be sustained upon examination by a taxing authority. Management considers, among other factors, the Company&#x2019;s current and past performance, the market environment in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	which the Company operates, and tax planning strategies. Further, the Company provides for income tax issues not yet resolved with federal, state, local, and foreign tax authorities. The Company assesses and updates its tax positions when significant changes in circumstances occur, which may cause a change in judgment about the likelihood of realizing the deferred items. Changes in circumstances or judgment about tax positions may cause a change in the Com
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	pany&#x2019;s uncertain tax position.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Variations in the actual outcome of these future tax consequences could materially impact the Company&#x2019;s results of operations
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	financial position
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and liquidity
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	S
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ee Note
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	to the Consolidated Financial Statements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	for additional
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	information regar
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ding
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the Company&#x2019;s income taxes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Defined Benefit Pension and Other Postretirement Benefit Plans
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The defined benefit pension and other postretirement benefit plan
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s were frozen as of March 2009.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The pension expenses and benefit obligations recorded for the Company&#x2019;s defined benefit plans are depen
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	dent on actuarial assumptions.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	These assumptions include discount rates, expected return on plan assets, interest costs, expected compensation increases, benefits earned, mortality rates, and other factors. Management review
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s the plan assumptions on an annual basis to ensure that the most current, relevant information is considered. During fiscal 2014, the Company adopted the RP-2014 mortality tables and the Mortality Improvement Scale MP-2014 published by the Society of Actuaries&#x2019; Retirement Plans Experience Committee.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The pension expense for fiscal year 2014 was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	derived based on the 2013 IRS Static Mortality table, while the pension expense for fiscal year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6 and 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	was derived based on the RP-2014 Mortality Table with Scale MP, to reflect future mortality improvements.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	If actual results vary considerably from those that are expected or if future changes are made
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	to these assumptions, the amounts recognized for these plans could change significantly.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The weighted-average assumed discount rates used to determine plan expenses

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	were 4.

	%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	for pension
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	benefits
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	3.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	% for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	other benefits in fiscal 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, compared to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

	4.14% for pension benefits and 3.40% for other benefits in fiscal 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. For fiscal 201
</FONT>

	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	expense, the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	expected
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	long-term rate of return of plan assets
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	was 6.50
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	%, unchanged from fiscal 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. In establishing the rate, management considered the historical rates of return and the current and planned asset classes of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the plan investment portfolio.
</FONT>

	The weighted-average discount rate used to determine benefit obligations at September&nbsp;30, 201

	35

</FONT>

	.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company recognizes on its balance sheet the amount by which the projected benefit obligations of its defined benefit plans exceed the fair value of plan assets. Subsequent changes in the funded status of the plans as a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	result of future transactions and events, amortization of previously unrecognized costs, and changes to actuarial assumptions are recognized as an asset or a liability and amortized as components of net periodic pension cost or accumulated other comprehensive income. An increase or decrease in the assumptions or economic events outside of management&#x2019;s control could have a material effect on the Company&#x2019;s results of operations or financial condition.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	S
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ee Note 1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	to the Consolidated Financial Statements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	for additional
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	information regar
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ding
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	these
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	benefit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	plans
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Stock-Based Compensation
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company measures and recognizes compensation cost at fair value for all stock-based awards, net of the estimated impact of forfeited
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	awards. The Company has not granted stock options subsequent to fiscal 2005. The fair values of options were estimated using a Black-Scholes option pricing model. In addition to stock options, key employees and/or non-employee directors are eligible to receive performance shares and restricted stock.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	U
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	nder the Company&#x2019;s 2016 Incentive Compensation Plan adopted in February 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, the fair value of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	restricted stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and performance shares
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	granted under the new plan is based on the Company&#x2019;s closing stock price on the grant date.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Stock-based c
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ompensation expense for restricted stock is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	cliff vested and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	recognized ratably over the vesting period.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The terms of performance share awards allow the recipients of such awards to earn a variable number of shares based on the achievement of the performance
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	goals specified in the awards.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Stock-based compensation expense associated with performance share awards is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	cliff vested and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	recognized based on management&#x2019;s best estimates of the achievement of the performance goals specified in such awards and the resulting number of shares that are expected to be earned. The Company evaluates on a quarterly basis the progress towards
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	achieving the performance criteria. The cumulative effect on current and prior periods of a change in the estimated number of performance share awards expected to be earned is recognized as compensation cost or as a reduction of cost in the period of the revised estimate. The Company also retains the discretion to make additional awards to executives at other times for recr
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	uiting or retention purposes.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Stock-based compensation for these awards can be either cliff or graded vested depending on the agreement, and recognized ratably over the vesting period.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	36
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;

<A NAME="eolPage37"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Forfeitures of awards are estimated at the time of grant and stock-based compensation cost is recognized only for those awards expected to vest. The Company uses historical experience to estimate projected forfeitures. The Company recognizes the cumulative effect on current and prior periods of a change in the forfeiture rate, or actual forfeitures, as compensation cost or as a reduction of cost in the period of the revision. If revisions are made to management&#x2019;s assumptions and estimates or if actual results vary considerably from those that are expected, stock-based compensation expense could change
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	significantly, impacting the Company&#x2019;s results of operations or financial condition.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;S
</FONT>

	ee Note 1

	4

	to the Consolidated Financial Statements

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	for additional
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	information regar
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ding
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the Company&#x2019;s stock-based awards
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Recent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Accounting Pronouncements
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	See Note 1 to the Consolidated Financial Statements

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Inflation
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company strives to reflect the inflationary impact of materials, labor and other operating costs and expenses in its prices. The market for the services and products that the Company offers, however, is highly competitive, and in some cases has limited the ability of the Company to offset inflationary cost increases.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 9PT">

	&#xFEFF;

<EFX_MARKET_RISK>
<A NAME="FIS_MARKET_RISK"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<A NAME="LDR-20160930X10K_HTM_QANDQMARKETRISK">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Item 7A.&nbsp;&nbsp;Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures about Market Risk
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company is exposed to market risk, including changes in foreign currency exchange rates. The financial statements of the Company&#x2019;s international subsidiaries are remeasured into U.S. dollars
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	monthly
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	using the U.S. dollar as the reporting currency. To date, the market risk associated with foreign currency exchange rates has not been material in relation to the Company&#x2019;s financial position, results of operations, or cash flows. These risks could increase, however, as the Company expands in international markets and markets becomes more volatile. The Company estimates that a 10% and 20% adverse change in the underlying foreign currency exchange rates would have decreased reported net income in fiscal 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	by approximately $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	0.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million and $1.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	million, respectively. Historically, the Company believes that adverse changes in foreign exchange rates have not materially impacted its financial condition.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company is subject to interest rate risk related to borrowings under the credit facility. The variable rate identified is based on L
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	IBOR plus a calculated margin.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	S
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ee Note 1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	to the Consolidated Financial Statements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	for additional
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	information regar
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ding
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the credit facility.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">

<EFX_AUDITORS_OPINION>
<A NAME="FIS_AUDITORS_OPINION"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<A NAME="LDR-20160930X10K_HTM_REPORTOFAUDITORS">
</A>
<A NAME="LDR-20160930X10K_HTM_FINANCIALSTATEMENTS">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Report of Independent Registered Public Accounting Firm
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Board of Directors and Stockholders
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Landauer, Inc.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Glenwood, Illinois
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	We have audited the accompanying consolidated balance sheets of Landauer, Inc. and its subsidiaries as of September 30, 2016 and 2015 and the related consolidated statements of operations and comprehensive income, stockholders&#x2019; equity, and cash flows for each of the two years in the period ended September 30, 2016. In connection with our audits of the financial statements, we have also audited the financial statement schedule listed in the accompanying index. These financial statements are the responsibility of the Company&#x2019;s management.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our responsibility is to express an opinion on these financial statements based on our audits.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	We conducted our audits in accordance with the standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States).&nbsp;&nbsp;Those standards require that we plan and perform the audit to obtain reasonable assurance about whether the financial statements are free of material misstatement. An audit also includes examining, on a test basis, evidence supporting the amounts and disclosures in the consolidated financial statements, assessing the accounting principles used and significant estimates made by management, as well as evaluating the overall presentation of the consolidated financial statements and schedule.&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe that our audits provide a reasonable basis for our opinion.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	In our opinion, the consolidated financial statements referred to above present fairly, in all material respects, the financial position of Landauer, Inc. and its subsidiaries at September 30, 2016 and 2015, and the results of its operations and its cash flows for each of the two years in the period ended September 30, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	in conformity with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States of America.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 4.7PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Also, in our opinion, the financial statement schedule, when considered in relation to the basic consolidated financial statements taken as a whole, present fairly, in all material respects, the information set forth therein.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 4.7PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	We also have audited, in accordance with the standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States), Landauer, Inc.&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting as of September 30, 2016, based on criteria established in Internal Control &#x2013; Integrated Framework (2013) issued by the Committee of Sponsoring Organizations of the Treadway Commission (COSO) and our report dated December 14, 2016, expressed an unqualified opinion thereon.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;COLOR:#FF00FF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Report of Independent Registered Public Accounting Firm
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;

</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	To the Stockholders and Board of Directors of Landauer, Inc.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In our opinion, the consolidated statements of operations, comprehensive income (loss), stockholders&#x2019; equity and cash flows for the year ended September 30, 2014 present fairly, in all material respects, the results of operations and cash flows of Landauer, Inc. and its subsidiaries for the year ended September 30, 2014, in conformity with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States of America.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, in our opinion, the financial statement schedule listed in the index appearing under Item 15(a)(2) for the year ended September 30, 2014 presents fairly, in all material respects, the information set forth therein when read in conjunction with the related consolidated financial statements.&nbsp;&nbsp;These financial statements and financial statement schedule are the responsibility of the Company's management.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our responsibility is to express an opinion on these financial statements and financial statement schedule based on our audit.&nbsp;&nbsp;We conducted our audit of these financial statements in accordance with the standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States).&nbsp;&nbsp;Those standards require that we plan and perform the audit to obtain reasonable assurance about whether the financial statements are free of material misstatement.&nbsp;&nbsp;An audit includes examining, on a test basis, evidence supporting the amounts and disclosures in the financial statements, assessing the accounting principles used and significant estimates made by management, and evaluating the overall financial statement presentation.&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe that our audit provides a reasonable basis for our opinion.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;

</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Notes to Consolidated Financial Statements
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	(Dollars in t
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	housands)

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 1PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:1PT;">
	&#xFEFF;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 11PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;;FONT-SIZE: 11PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
</FONT>
<A NAME="LDR-20160930X10K_HTM_SUMMARYSIGACCOUNTINGPOLICIES">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Summary of Significant Accounting Policies
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Description of Business
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Landauer
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, Inc., together with the subsidiaries through which businesses are conducted (the &#x201C;Company&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	is a leading global provider of technical and analytical services to determine occupational and environmental radiation exposure
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the leading domestic provider of outsourced medical physics services
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, and a provider of radiology related medical products
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The Company operates in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	t
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	hree
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	primary business segments
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	:
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Radiation Measurement
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Medical Physics
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	; and Medical Products
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	(divested in May 2016)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Additional i
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	nformation regarding the Company&#x2019;s segments is contained in Note
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Basis of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Presentation and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Consolidation
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The consolidated financial statements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	have been prepared in accordance with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States of America (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	U.S. GAAP&#x201D;) and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	include the accounts of the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	its subsidiaries. All intercompany balances and transactions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	have been
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	eliminated in consolidation. Entities in which the Company does not have a controlling financial interest
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	but is considered to have significant influence
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	are accounted for on the equity method.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Use of Estimates
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The preparation of financial statements in conformity with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	U.S. GAAP
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	requires management to make estimates and assumptions that affect the reported amounts of assets and liabilities and disclosure of contingent assets and liabilities at the date of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	consolidated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	financial statements and the reported amounts of revenues and expenses during the reporting period. Actual results could differ from those estimates.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Cash and Cash Equivalents
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Cash and cash equivalents include
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	all unrestricted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	cash and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	highly liquid
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	investments with an original maturity of three months or less
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	primarily short-term money market instruments.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Receivables
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	, Net of Allowances
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	R
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	eceivable
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	, principally trade
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	accounts receivable
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	, are generally due within
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	30
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	90
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	days and are stated at amounts due from customers, net of an allowance for sales returns and doubtful accounts.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	perform
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	ongoing credit evaluations of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	customers and adjust
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	credit limits based upon payment history and the customer&#x2019;s current creditworthiness, as determined by a review of their current credit information. We continuously monitor aging reports, collections and payments from customers, and a provision for estimated credit losses is maintained based upon
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	the Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	historical experience and any specific customer collection issues that have been identified. While such credit losses have historically been within our expectations and the provisions established, we cannot guarantee that the same credit loss rates will be experienced in the future.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	write
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	off accounts receivable when they are determined to be uncollectible.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Inventories
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Inventories
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	primarily include
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	the components associated with dosimetry devices,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	stated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;COLOR:#000000;">
	at lower of cost or market utilizing a first-in, first-out method.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Long-lived Assets
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Property, plant and equipment are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	stated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	at cost
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	net of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	accumulated depreciation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and amortization
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. Plant, equipment and internal
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	use
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	software are depreciated on a straight-line basis over their
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	respective
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	estimated useful lives. Dosimetry devices, principally badges, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the accompanying
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	software are amortized on a straight-line basis over their estimated useful lives.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Expenditures for m
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	aintenance and repairs are charged to expense
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	as incurred
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, and
</FONT>
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
